catalog.title: Human Genetic Diseases
catalog.description: The aim of this class is to help students gain a sufficient understanding of human genetics so that they can appreciate the genetic basis of human disease, and the importance of genetic considerations in the prevention and treatment of diseases. This course will use a literature-based approach to cover the fundamentals, from the chromosomal basis for hereditary to the molecular and biochemical basis of genetic diseases as well as the current molecular diagnostic and treatment methods available for genetic diseases. A combination of classic and current papers, together with case studies will be used. The course is aimed at students in biology and related fields with a keen interest in human disease. This class is dual listed with BIO 433.

catalog.title: Foundations of DevoEvo
catalog.description: This course examines the historical and conceptual foundations of Developmental Evolution (DevoEvo) through readings and group discussions of historical and philosophical literature on origins of and reception to evolutionary and developmental biology, in particular the role developmental phenomena played in the formulation of evolutionary ideas.

catalog.title: Cancer Immunology
catalog.description: This course is designed to provide students an understanding of the interplay between tumors and the immune system, as well as current therapies that use the immune system in the setting of oncology. This course is dual listed with BIO 424.
catalog.subject: Biological Sciences

Take Note of Prerequisites

The primary goal of this course to teach graduate students, who are actively involved in research to understand quantitative and statistical concepts. Specifically, throughout the course, the students will learn fundamental statistical concepts relevant to biological sciences with the ultimate goal of conceptualizing study designs in different subfields of biology. There will be a computational laboratory component where basic statistical analysis on data will be performed using R statistical package. No prior knowledge of R is required.
